<span id="ii.iii.v-p1"></span> <span class="c4"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p1.1"></span>Authorities and Materials.</span>

<span id="ii.iii.v-p2"></span>The chief ancient and medieval authorities
for the life and times of Leo the Great are such works as *Prosper’s*,
and *Idatius’ Chronicles, Iornandes de rebus Geticis, Anastasius
Bibliothecarius Historia de vitis Romanorum Pontificum* (9th cent.), the
*Historia Miscella* (10th cent.), &c.

<span id="ii.iii.v-p3"></span>Among *lives* may be mentioned the
following:—(1) *<span id="ii.iii.v-p3.1"></span>La vie et religion de
deux bons papes Léon premier et Gregoire premier par* <span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.2"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.3"></span>Pierre Du Moulin</span> (the younger:  a
protestant theologian), *Sedan*, 1650. 12mo.  (2) <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.4"></span>Quesnel’s</span> valuable *Dissertatio de vita
et rebus gestis S. Leonis Magni*, originally included in his edition of
Leo and re-printed by Migne in Vol. ii. of his edition with the
Ballerinii’s annotations and critical remarks, *Paris*, 1675, *Lyons*,
1700.  (3) *<span id="ii.iii.v-p3.5"></span>Histoire du Pontificat de
Saint Léon le Grand par Monsr. L. Maimbourg La Haye*, 1687.  (4) *The
Bollandists’ Life by Canisius* (*Acta Sanctorum*), *April*, vol. ii. pp.
14–22.  (5) <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.6"></span>Alphonsi</span> <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.7"></span>Ciaconii</span> *Vitæ Pontificum* (*Tom.* 1,
pp. 303–314), *Rome*, 1677, 4*to*.  (6) <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.8"></span>Le Nain de Tillemont</span><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.9"></span>, *Memoires pour servir à l’histoire
Ecclesiastique* (vol. xv. pp. 414–832, 885–934), *Paris*, 1711.  (7)
<span id="page_xv">p. xv</span> <span
id="ii.iii.v-Page_xv"></span>*Breve Descrizione della vita di S. Leone
Primo di* <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.10"></span>Gabrielle</span> <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.11"></span>Bertazzolo</span>:  *Mantova*, 1727.  (8)
*Memoire istoriche di Sa. Leone Papa da* <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.12"></span>Teofilo</span> <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.13"></span>Pacifico</span>:  *Brescia*, 1791, 8*vo*. 
(9) <span class="sc"><span id="ii.iii.v-p3.14"></span>Du Pin</span>, L.
E., *History of Ecc. writers* (Eng Edn. vol. 1, pp. 464–480), *Dublin*,
1722.  (10) C. <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.15"></span>Oudinus</span>, *de Scriptoribus Ecclesiæ*
(vol. 1, pp. 1271–5), *Leipzig*, 1722.  (11) <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.16"></span>Wilhelm</span> <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.17"></span>Amadeus</span> <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.18"></span>Arendt</span> (*Roman Catholic*), *Leo der
Grosse und seine Zeit, Mainz*, 1835, 8*vo*.  (12) <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.19"></span>Eduard</span> <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.20"></span>Perthel</span>, *Papst Leo’s I. Leben und
Lehren, Jena*, 1843, 8*vo*. (a counterblast to No. 11, and no less
exaggerated and prejudiced in statement).  (13) A. <span
class="sc"><span id="ii.iii.v-p3.21"></span>de Saint-Chron</span>,
*<span id="ii.iii.v-p3.22"></span>Histoire du pontificat de Saint Léon
le Grand, Paris*, 1846.  (14) F. <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.23"></span>Böhringer</span>, *die Kirche Xti und ihre
Zeugen* (vol. 1 part 4, pp. 170–309), *Zürich*, 1845.  (15) <span
class="sc"><span id="ii.iii.v-p3.24"></span>Charles</span> <span
class="sc"><span id="ii.iii.v-p3.25"></span>Gore’s</span> *Life of Leo
the Great* (S.P.C.K.); also his article in Smith’s *Dict. of Christian
Biogr*.  (16) The article in <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.26"></span>Herzog’s</span> *Real-Encyklopädie* of which
a condensed English edition was edited by Dr. Philip Schaff at New York
in 1883.  Other more general accounts of his times will be found in (1)
l’abbé <span class="sc"><span id="ii.iii.v-p3.27"></span>Fleury</span>,
*<span id="ii.iii.v-p3.28"></span>Histoire du Xtianisme* (vol. ii. pp.
384–480), *Paris*, 1836.  (2) <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.29"></span>Bright’s</span> *History of the Church from*
313–451 (chaps. xiv., xv.), *Oxford and London*, 1860.  (3) <span
class="sc"><span id="ii.iii.v-p3.30"></span>Milman’s</span> *Latin
Christianity* (Book ii. chap. 4), *London*, 1864.  (4) R. J. <span
class="sc"><span id="ii.iii.v-p3.31"></span>Rohrbacher’s</span> *<span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.32"></span>Histoire Universelle de l’Eglise catholique*
(15th edn., vol. 4, pp. 461–575), *Paris*, 1868.  A short account of
Leo’s writings is given in <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.33"></span>Alzog’s</span> *Grundriss der Patrologie*, §
78, pp.368–375:  a most exhaustive one in <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.34"></span>Ceillier’s</span> *<span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.35"></span>Histoire générale des Auteurs sacrés* (new
edition) (vol. x., pp. 169–276), 1858–1869.  <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.36"></span>Bähr’s</span> *Geschichte der Römischer
Literatur-Supplement Band II. Abtheilung* (pp. 354–362), *im Abendland*,
vol. 1, p. 448, may also be consulted; and <span class="sc"><span
id="ii.iii.v-p3.37"></span>Ebert’s</span> *Allgemeine Geschichte der
Literatur des Mittelalters*.

